      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:10:1",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا الْحَسَنِ الرِّضَا ( عليه السلام ) عَنِ الرَّجُلِ يُدَبِّرُ الْمَمْلُوكَ وَ هُوَ حَسَنُ الْحَالِ ثُمَّ يَحْتَاجُ هَلْ يَجُوزُ لَهُ أَنْ يَبِيعَهُ قَالَ نَعَمْ إِذَا احْتَاجَ إِلَى ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Husayn Bin Muhammad, from Moala Bin Muhammad, from Al Washa whom said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Al-Hassan Al-Reza<sup>asws</sup> the man who arranged (the emancipation of) the owned slave and he was of good (financial) condition. Then he became needy. Is it allowed for him to sell him?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Yes, when he is need for that’."
        ]
      }
    }
